cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks for visual perception tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the training of these networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.NE, cs.LG). The implications of the results for using artificial networks to study human vision suggest a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
